properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 9 at 3:03AM CST until February 9 at 3:00PM CST by NWS Quad Cities IA IL
properties.description:
...Accumulating Snow Today...

.A fast moving storm system will bring a round of snow to the
area. Light snow will begin developing just prior to sunrise and
will increase in coverage and intensity during the morning.

From mid morning into the early afternoon, moderate to briefly
heavy snow is possible with snowfall rates approaching 1 inch per
hour. The main impacts from the snow will be slippery roads and
significantly reduced visibilities.

* WHAT...Snow expected. Total snow accumulations of 1 to 2 inches.
Winds gusting up to 30 mph.

* WHERE...Portions of east central Iowa and north central and
northwest Illinois.

* WHEN...From 9 AM this morning to 3 PM CST this afternoon.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions and significantly
reduced visibilities.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...The heaviest snow rates are expected to
fall from mid morning to early afternoon. Up to 1 inch per hour
is possible.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

In Illinois, go to www.gettingaroundillinois.com for road
conditions.
In Iowa, call 511 for road conditions.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY IN EFFECT FROM 9 AM THIS MORNING TO 3 PM CST THIS AFTERNOON
